# <type>(<scope>): <subject>
#
# <body>
#
# <footer>

# Type should be one of the following:
# * feat: A new feature
# * fix: A bug fix
# * docs: Documentation only changes
# * style: Changes that do not affect the meaning of the code (white-space, formatting, missing semi-colons, etc)
# * refactor: A code change that neither fixes a bug nor adds a feature
# * perf: A code change that improves performance
# * test: Adding missing tests or correcting existing tests
# * chore: Changes to the build process or auxiliary tools and libraries such as documentation generation
# * ci: Changes to our CI configuration files and scripts
# * build: Changes that affect the build system or external dependencies
# * revert: Reverts a previous commit

# Scope should be one of the following:
# * web-storefront: Changes to the web storefront app
# * web-admin: Changes to the web admin app
# * api-gateway: Changes to the API gateway
# * domain: Changes to the domain package
# * infra: Changes to the infrastructure package
# * ui: Changes to the UI package
# * config: Changes to the config package
# * contracts: Changes to the contracts package
# * orders-worker: Changes to the orders worker service
# * background-worker: Changes to the background worker service
# * docker: Changes to Docker configuration
# * ci: Changes to CI/CD configuration
# * docs: Changes to documentation

# Subject should be:
# * imperative, present tense: "change" not "changed" nor "changes"
# * not capitalized: "add feature" not "Add feature"
# * no period (.) at the end

# Body should be:
# * imperative, present tense
# * include motivation for the change and contrast with previous behavior
# * wrap at 72 characters
# * use blank line to separate from subject

# Footer should be:
# * reference any issues that this commit closes
# * include any breaking changes
# * include any migration notes

# Examples:
# feat(api-gateway): add rate limiting middleware
#
# Add express-rate-limit middleware to prevent abuse of API endpoints.
# Configure different rate limits for different routes based on their
# sensitivity and expected usage patterns.
#
# Closes #123
# Breaking change: API rate limits are now enforced

# fix(web-storefront): resolve product image loading issue
#
# Fix issue where product images were not loading due to incorrect
# URL construction in the image component. The issue was caused by
# missing base URL configuration in the image loader.
#
# Closes #456

